				\begin{document}$$\rho =1-\frac{6\sum {d}_{i}^{2}}{n({n}^{2}-1)}$$\end{document}ρ=1−6∑di2n(n2−1)where d is the difference of the rank given by two different centralities for one gene and n is the total number of nodes or genes. The coefficient ρ can range from −1 to 1 where 1 stands for perfectly positive correlation zero (0) for no correlation and −1 perfectly negative correlation.
